<b>Subject:</b> Perhaps your point was lost in all your name calling.....<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=808" TARGET=_self>Re: Read this my holier than thou freind</A> (dylan waite)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>Re-read your post my friend. It is laced with name calling and judgements on the PvP community. Anytime you litter a post with name calling you are going to have your arguement missed or flatly ignored. Your post was only "flammable" becuase of it's content not becuase of what I read or didn't read. You postcame across to be as bitter and rittled with a "time to get even" attitude. You obviously feel that UO was ruined by PvP, and so you see an opportunity to do the same to us. We didn't write the code or release a beta product as a final product.....that was Origin. Please don't hold all of us responsible for their short commings.

<P>It is clear that EQ will seperate PvP+ and PvP- people very efficently, therefore you won't have to worry about any "L33t" "snot nosed Jr High jerks" ruining the game. This being a fact, your types of posts are fruitless and do not help further the purpose of this board. Thats all I was trying to say. I agree that those that choose to not participate in PvP should not be forced to. Hopefully they will have their servers and we will have ours. There problem solved. I for one don't worry about the more immature players, I simply kill them till they stop doing whatever it was that bothered me. This works eventually most of the time, and it's fun for me to boot.
<P>I'm also curious are you even playing on the PvP server? or plan to in final?
<P>&gt; how many times will i have to respond to ignorant commentary
<BR>&gt; about posts i have made?.....i'm beginning to wonder....it seems
<BR>&gt; YOU ALSO have missed my point in your haste to flame
<BR>&gt; someone......I NEVER SUGGESTED THAT THE l3TT WERE THE NORM IN
<BR>&gt; THE PVP COMMUNITY, I ONLY STATED THAT THEY CERTAINLY EXIST AND
<BR>&gt; WILL BE THE ONES WHO ARE ABLE TO RUIN LEGITIMATE PVP FOR THE
<BR>&gt; REST OF US, HENCE, THEY MUST CONTROLLED......seriously folks,
<BR>&gt; how many times can a guy say the same goddam thing before he
<BR>&gt; begins to get a little frustrated....can it be that you're all
<BR>&gt; just so desperate for a flame war that you'll ignore the facts
<BR>&gt; in someone's post for that fact that the post may be construed
<BR>&gt; as flammable
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
